# Class: <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620036> (tile drain decommissioning process)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620036> "A mechanical hydrological alteration process in which a human decommissions subterranean tile drains by collapsing them in situ or by excavating and removing them, in order to reduce drainage and restore wetland hydroperiod."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620036> "This term consolidates the formerly separate tile drain crushing process and tile drain removal process, as both achieve the same management goal by similar means."@en)
