AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620628> "A biological ecosystem management process in which a human provides supplemental water sources for wild fauna in areas where natural water availability is limited. Examples include constructing artificial ponds, guzzlers, or placing temporary water troughs for wildlife during drought. Distinct from irrigation process, which provides water to plants."@en)
