AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621045> "A biological ecosystem management process in which a human implements measures to prevent, detect, or reduce the spread of infectious diseases in wild fauna populations, in order to protect individual animals or conserve threatened species. Methods may include vaccination, treatment, culling of diseased individuals, or management of disease transmission pathways."@en)
