# Class: <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> (rewetting process)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> "A mechanical hydrological alteration process in which a human raises the water table of a degraded terrestrial or wetland area by blocking drainage structures, filling drainage channels, or otherwise impeding water loss, in order to restore hydrological function."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4366-3088>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4817-0423>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#created_by> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#creation_date> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> "2026-07-07"^^xsd:dateTime)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> "rewetting"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> "Peatland rewetting process (ELMO:3620646) is a narrower term applicable specifically to peatlands."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> "rewetting process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broadMatch> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> <https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3>)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/elmo/property/hasCASCode> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> "2.3")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621052> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620033>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> (site preparation process)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> "A mechanical ecosystem management process in which a human modifies the physical, chemical, or biological conditions of a site prior to vegetation establishment, in order to improve conditions for seedling germination and plant establishment."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4366-3088>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4817-0423>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#created_by> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#creation_date> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> "2026-07-07"^^xsd:dateTime)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> "site prep"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> "site preparation process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broadMatch> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> <https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3>)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/elmo/property/hasCASCode> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> "2.3")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620020>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> (soil scarification process)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> "A site preparation process in which a human mechanically disturbs the soil surface or duff layer, typically using a disc, rake, or roller, to expose mineral soil and create a favourable seedbed for germination and seedling establishment."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4366-3088>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4817-0423>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#created_by> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1296-2528>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#creation_date> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> "2026-07-07"^^xsd:dateTime)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> "scarification (seedbed)"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> "Distinct from seed scarification process (ELMO:3620617), which refers to mechanical abrasion of seed coats to break dormancy. In restoration literature the term 'scarification' often refers to this soil-level treatment."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> "soil scarification process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broadMatch> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> <https://w3id.org/elmo/cas/2.3>)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/elmo/property/hasCASCode> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> "2.3")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621054> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621053>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621055> (transplanting process)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621055> "A plant material transfer process in which a human removes whole rooted plants from a source location and establishes them at a restoration site, retaining the root system to promote post-transfer survival."@en)
